Use kagome.sh script for control you kagome's docker-containers

Just call this with one of follow arguments

First of all, you should create build environment
 kagome.sh build_env   - create docker container image with packages for configure and compile
 kagome.sh publish_env - publish this to dockerhub for using in autockeck pipelines, continuous integration, etc.

Build binaries of kagome
 kagome.sh build       - pull required images and repo, build binaries and make kagome docker-image

Distribution:
 kagome.sh publish     - push docker on dockerhub

